# Visual Identity

The game should feel like:

* Opening an old dictionary.
* Reading an old government training manual.
* Working through official language exercises.
* Vintage.
* Warm.
* Calm.

Not modern neon.

Not cartoon.

Not childish.

Think:

* aged paper
* dark walnut wood
* brass/gold accents
* black ink
* olive-green buttons

The visual style itself should communicate:

> "This is where serious word mastery happens."

That identity would immediately separate your game from the bright, colorful look used by most existing word games.
